## Variety

One of the very best things about growing your own food is that you can enjoy a much greater variety than you can find in shops.  Broadly speaking, the varieties you find in shops are ones that were selectively chosen year after year that were resistant to pest and disease, uniform in shape and size and looked great on the shelf making them easy to sell.  Nothing in there about taste or variety.  Choose things you enjoy eating most and are suitable to your available space.  Try growing something you haven't tasted before.

